title: Grateful Dead Live at StadtHalle on 1981-10-10
description: Shakedown Street-> Bertha-> Minglewood Blues, Friend Of The Devil-> El Paso, Tennessee Jed, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Bird Song, Let It Grow-> Deal Women Are Smarter, Sugaree, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Truckin'-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> One More Saturday Night, E: Casey Jones

reviews.review_text: good not great, but good Some might go one star more--vocals are a little out front, but tempos don't get too loggy, nice Sugaree, Jerry pushes the pace of Eyes of the World. fans of the 80's should enjoy this very much. Worth downloading.
eyes of the world great eyes!

Give this show a chance! The Compendium was overly harsh on this show. It would get more respect if the Melkweg shows did not follow it. Nice bass unlike most of fall Europe '81. Great FOTD, Space (Go Phil!), and sweet Eyes!

Fastest Eyes Ever Love Bobby's energy is St. of Circumstance, one of the Fastest Eye's I've heard!
Great qualtiy
Where's Jerry? Jerry is either very low or absent in the mix until Tenn. Jed.  However the Birdsong, LIG>Deal and the lightning quick Eyes are excellent.

Meh Bobby blows lyrics right and left. The playing by the guys is in general pretty good. Eyes is WAY to fast but is enjoyable for the novelty. Space is good as is the Other One but overall this show is only OK in my estimation, not bad by any means, just average.

Generaly I'd like to put out a big THANK YOU to all the people who are involved in this wonderful site.
Don't want to rate anything. I'm just grateful for listening to so much beautiful music.
This show stands for many, many other great and for shure better ones than this...
In music and atmospere I love 70's Grateful Dead with Keith... Philosophy?... All times. 
Why I review this one?... Very simple... It was my first and only...
and the beginning of a love, I'm falling in... now for the 257th... or so... time 
THANK YOU.
Enjoyable Highlights: Let It Grow, Deal, Eyes Of The World

Did I change the time rate? Listening to the brilliant Eyes of the World I am perplexed, did I accidentally turn on x1.25 or x1.50 play speed? Oh no that’s right, this is 1981 and everyone is gakked to the gills! LOL, it’s true though I love these super fast 80s burner renditions. Overall, great show, great era, buy the ticket/take the ride! (~);} 2404 NFA
